HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 63
BY REPRESENTATIVE MIKE JOHNSON
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Dr. Mark Johnson on his inauguration as president of
Louisiana Christian University and commemorates 120 years of the university's
academic excellence, faith, and service
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Dr. Mark Johnson on his inauguration as president of Louisiana Christian
3 University and to commemorate one hundred twenty years of academic excellence,
4 faith, and service to the state of Louisiana and beyond.
5 WHEREAS, Louisiana Christian University was founded in 1906 and has faithfully
6 served the state of Louisiana and the nation for one hundred twenty years by providing
7 Christ-centered higher education and cultivating generations of leaders grounded in faith,
8 integrity, and scholarship; and
9 WHEREAS, throughout its distinguished history, the university has remained
10 steadfast in its mission to prepare students for lives of learning, leadership, and service and
11 made a lasting impact on central Louisiana and communities across the nation; and
12 WHEREAS, the inauguration of Dr. Mark Johnson as president marks a significant
13 and celebratory milestone in the university's enduring legacy and ushers in a new era of
14 visionary leadership, continued growth, and strengthened commitment to academic and
15 spiritual excellence; and
16 WHEREAS, Dr. Johnson's leadership reflects a dedication to advancing the mission
17 of Louisiana Christian University while honoring its rich heritage and positioning the
18 institution for continued success in the years ahead; and
